Subject:  Base Metal Matter




 Dear Arthur and Martin:
 I received late this evening a rather outrageous letter from Ely Goldin in
which he takes the position that our documents "raise more questions than
they answer." He also indicates that he sees no purpose in having a
conference call unless it is to discuss our responses to his discovery
requests served upon us earlier today, which, incidentally, are completely
void and of no effect under the US Federal Rules of Civil Procedure in my
considered judgement.
 I will separately attempt to email to you Goldin's letter, but, in the
event technology fails me, will also fax it to you first thing Friday
morning.
 I believe we should go forward with the conference call among ourselves to
agree upon the next actions on our part. As we suspected, the Base Metal
people are plainly going to be anything but reasonable and, unfortunately,
we will almost certainly be forced to seek our relief from the Court, rathe=
r
than through business like discussions with them.
 I believe you already have dial in instructions for the 10:30 am EDT
conference call. If not, let me know and I'll get them to you.
 I look forward to speaking to you in the am.

Mark

